pullRequest.body:
Given a commutative ring `k` and a group `G`, this file shows that a short exact sequence of
`k`-linear `G`-representations `0 ‚ü∂ X‚ÇÅ ‚ü∂ X‚ÇÇ ‚ü∂ X‚ÇÉ ‚ü∂ 0` induces a short exact sequence of
complexes of inhomogeneous chains `0 ‚ü∂ C(X‚ÇÅ) ‚ü∂ C(X‚ÇÇ) ‚ü∂ C(X‚ÇÉ) ‚ü∂ 0`, where `H‚Çô(C(X·µ¢))`
is the `n`th group homology of `X·µ¢`.
This allows us to specialize API about long exact sequences to group homology; in this PR we focus on degrees `n = 0, 1, 2`.
